i wanted this video to highlight people whose voices i look to when i need to be reminded of my own power. people who not only hope for a better world but do everything they can to make it better everyday. check out the video and don’t forget “loudmouth” the al sharpton doc comes out today! 💜💜💜

extremely grateful for the chance to perform at the white house yesterday. 

the signing of the respect for marriage act means a lot to me as a queer human. yes, it means that i have the ability to marry someone i love but i think it also serves as a reminder that the loving and accepting world i longed for as a queer kid is not a myth. it's a reality that we have to build brick by brick every single day. grateful for the help of @potus and @vpotus for helping build that world and protect that reality.

maybe i was just inspired by the fact that the room i write most of my music in is covered in a massive collage. who's to say.

Joy Oladokun. Musician.
.
If you can, turn it up. Joy’s music has made it on more ones-to-watch lists than we have room for. She’s soulful with a silver lining, and she’s making change through Nashville Launch Pad, a cold-weather shelter for all youth, specifically LGBTQ+ youth, in Nashville. “As a child I was scared to be truthful about who I was, so advocating for kids experiencing the same thing is very important for me,” Joy shared.

i went and became a gap model on accident.

i've loved gap's clothes forever. i've basically worn their jeans my entire life. to be asked to be a part of their campaign with @thebkcircus is a dream i didn't know that i had come true.

grateful to be on the cover of @nashvillianmag.

nashville has adopted and raised me in almost every way imaginable. i have become a better writer, musician, and human while living here. i feel like this city is full of people who heard me when almost everyone else was hellbent on ignoring me. to be on the cover of a magazine that i have images from on my studio wall means more than i really have words for. grab a copy where you can (if you want 😉)💜💜💜

wake up, kids. a new version of sweet symphony just dropped.
